August 20th 2022 9:05 am For many years I have enjoyed Caribou Coffee. Unfortunately the last few months I have consistently received incorrect drink orders. Wrong ingredients, wrong size, and completely incorrect orders. I have ordered the exact same drink for more than a decade. It's super easy, yet recently it has been a challenge to receive a correct order. I have never complained about mistakes until this morning. I ordered a large drink as always. I was handed a medium. When I questioned the order, the barista reprints the recept and shoves it in my face telling my I ordered a medium, and was showing no sign or urge to correct the mistake. No ma'am, I ordered a large and showing me the receipt only reinforces the fact my order was taken incorrectly. It doesn't matter what I was charged or what drink they made. I ordered a large as I always do, therefore the order was incorrect. The poor attitude and unwillingness to fix the mistake will definitely be preventing me from being a regular anymore.
